        jitApprovalMode: "string",
        jitApprovers: [{
            id: "string",
            displayName: "string",
            type: "string",
        }],
        maximumJitAccessDuration: "string",
    },
    identity: {
        type: azure_native.solutions.ResourceIdentityType.SystemAssigned,
        userAssignedIdentities: ["string"],
    },
    location: "string",
    applicationDefinitionId: "string",
    managedResourceGroupId: "string",
    parameters: "any",
    plan: {
        name: "string",
        product: "string",
        publisher: "string",
        version: "string",
        promotionCode: "string",
    },
    applicationName: "string",
    sku: {
        name: "string",
        capacity: 0,
        family: "string",
        model: "string",
        size: "string",
        tier: "string",
    },
    tags: {
        string: "string",
    },
});
```

</pulumi-choosable>

type: azure-native:solutions:Application
properties:
    applicationDefinitionId: string
    applicationName: string
    identity:

        jitApprovalMode: string
        jitApprovers:

              id: string
              type: string

    kind: string
    location: string
    managedBy: string
    managedResourceGroupId: string
    parameters: any
    plan:
        name: string
        product: string
        promotionCode: string
        publisher: string
        version: string
    resourceGroupName: string
    sku:
        capacity: 0
        family: string
        model: string
        name: string
        size: string
        tier: string
    tags:
        string: string
```

## Import



An existing resource can be imported using its type token, name, and identifier, e.g.

```sh
$ pulumi import azure-native:solutions:Application myManagedApplication /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Solutions/applications/{applicationName} 
```


To learn more about importing existing cloud resources, see [Importing resources](/docs/using-pulumi/adopting-pulumi/import/).
